The Anr parameter specifies a string on which to perform an ambiguous name resolution (ANR) search. It must be atleast three character in length. You can specify a partial string and search for objects with an attribute that matches that string. The default attributes searched are: CommonName(CN), DisplayName, FirstName, LastName, Alias

The SoftDeletedMailbox switch parameter specifies whether to include only soft-deleted mailboxes in the results.Possible values for this Parametr are True and False. Use Parameter value True to include only soft-deleted mailboxes.

The InactiveMailboxOnly switch parameter specifies whether to include only inactive mailboxes in the results.Possible values for this Parametr are True and False. Use Parameter value True to include only inactive mailboxes.

The Archive switch parameter specifies whether to include only Archive mailboxes in the results.Possible values for this Parametr are True and False. Use Parameter value True to include only Archive mailboxes.

The MailboxPlan parameter filters the results by mailbox plan.When you use this parameter, only mailboxes that are assigned the specified mailbox plan are returned in the results.You can use any value that uniquely identifies the mailbox plan like Name, Alias, Guid

The IncludeInactiveMailbox switch parameter specifies whether to include Inactive mailboxes in the results.When you use this switch, active and inactive mailboxes are included in the results.Possible values for this Parametr are True and False.

The RecipientTypeDetails parameter filters the results by the specified mailbox subtype. valid values are DiscoveryMailbox, EquipmentMailbox,GroupMailbox, LegacyMailbox, LinkedMailbox, LinkedRoomMailbox, RoomMailbox, SchedulingMailbox, SharedMailbox, TeamMailbox, UserMailbox.Multiple Recipient type Details can be combined using comma separted like SharedMailbox,UserMailbox,RoomMailbox

For example, /Mailbox(Identity)?isEncoded=true, says that the Identity is base64 encoded.Similarly for /Recipient/Exchange.GetRecipientPermissionByFilters(identity=Identity,trustee=Trustee Type,accessRight=Access Right)?isEncoded=true, says Identity and Trustee are base64 encoded

The Anr parameter specifies a string on which to perform an ambiguous name resolution (ANR) search. It must be atleast three character in length. You can specify a partial string and search for objects with an attribute that matches that string. The default attributes searched are: CommonName(CN), DisplayName, FirstName, LastName, Alias

The OrganizationalUnit parameter filters the results based on the object's location in Active Directory. Only objects that exist in the specified location are returned. Valid input for this parameter is an organizational unit (OU) or Org name or Org GUID or Org sistinguished name.
